        <updateDate>2021-09-02T14:00:13Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>IMF Afghan Recognition Assurance Act</strong></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of the Treasury to oppose any International Monetary Fund recognition of Afghanistan if the Taliban controls Afghanistan's government. </p> <p>The President may temporarily waive this requirement if (1) the Taliban-controlled government is upholding the rights of women and girls in Afghanistan, (2) the Taliban-controlled government is not providing support for international acts of terrorism or permitting terrorist groups to operate from Afghanistan, and (3) such a waiver supports U.S. national interests. </p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
